Testing Requirements

Every task must include unit tests.

Required test coverage
Happy path behavior for the new feature
At least one edge case for the new feature
Deterministic validation of outcomes
Mocked or seeded randomness where applicable
Example edge cases to cover
Drawing from an empty draw pile
Reshuffling when discard pile is empty
Trying to play a card with insufficient energy
Applying damage larger than current block
Overkill damage reducing health to zero but not below allowed bounds
Attempting invalid map traversal
Loading malformed or incomplete save data


Notes for Implementation Agents
Prefer small pure functions for combat and deck logic
Keep game state serializable
Avoid coupling UI code to core combat logic
Start with one player class and a very small card pool
Start with one basic enemy behavior before adding enemy variety
Do not add polish before the full playable loop works

